# FlowVault Integration — Environment Variables
#
# All VITE_FLOWVAULT_* vars are optional.
# The SDK ships with built-in DEFAULT_CONTRACTS for testnet and mainnet,
# so you only need to set these if you are targeting a custom deployment.
#
# Testnet defaults (SDK built-in):
#   Contract:  STD7QG84VQQ0C35SZM2EYTHZV4M8FQ0R7YNSQWPD.flowvault-v2
#   USDCx:     ST1PQHQKV0RJXZFY1DGX8MNSNYVE3VGZJSRTPGZGM.usdcx
#
# WARNING: Never mix testnet and mainnet contract principals.
# Rule from docs: keep contract and token principals from the same network.

# Optional: override the FlowVault contract deployer address
# VITE_FLOWVAULT_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=STD7QG84VQQ0C35SZM2EYTHZV4M8FQ0R7YNSQWPD

# Optional: override the FlowVault contract name
# VITE_FLOWVAULT_CONTRACT_NAME=flowvault-v2

# Optional: override the USDCx token contract address
# VITE_FLOWVAULT_TOKEN_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=ST1PQHQKV0RJXZFY1DGX8MNSNYVE3VGZJSRTPGZGM

# Optional: override the USDCx token contract name
# VITE_FLOWVAULT_TOKEN_CONTRACT_NAME=usdcx
